        "text": "Six days can work as a compact classic route if flight or train timing is sensible. It is better for travelers who accept a focused pace and do not need long slow stays in every destination."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Should I choose an 8-day Yunnan route if I want Shangri-La?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Usually yes. Shangri-La adds highland scenery and more travel distance, so an 8-day route is a safer starting point than trying to fit it into a very short trip."
